message.text:
Good day ITHM students,

For those who attended the Sports Fest General Orientation last August 27, please take note of the following reminders:

1. Submission of Requirements

Submit your signed waiver (signed by your parent or guardian) with a photocopy of their ID and your COR.

You may submit your complete requirements on the following schedule at ARH 504 faculty room or ARH Consultation room 506. Please look for the Sports Officers.

Schedule:

Tuesday: 10:30 am – 12:00 nn | 3:00 pm – 6:00 pm

Wednesday: 10:30 am – 6:00 pm

Thursday: 11:00 am – 6:00 pm

2. Attendance Verification
Before we accept your requirements, we will check if your name is on the attendance sheet from the Sports Fest General Orientation. If your name is not on the list, you will not be allowed to join the tryouts.

3. Deadline of Submission
No requirements will be accepted on the day of the tryouts. The last day of submission is Thursday.

4. During Tryouts

Participants are requested to come early for registration and a short briefing.

Orientation will start at 5:00 pm at the ARH 3rd Floor Function Room.

Do not proceed directly to the FEU Court/Quadrangle.

5. Proper Attire
Do not enter the university wearing your jersey. The guards will not allow you entry. Please change inside the campus.

6. In Case of Bad Weather
If classes are not suspended, the tryouts will push through. A Plan B will be implemented and announced during the briefing.

Lastly, during the Sports Fest General Orientation, we provided a QR code to join the official group chat for all attendees. If you are not yet part of it, kindly send us a message on our page.

REMEMBER:
NO ORIENTATION, NO TRYOUTS
NO TRYOUTS, NO SPORTS FEST

message.text:
Good day ITHM students,

For those who attended the Sports Fest General Orientation last August 27, please take note of the following reminders:

1. Submission of Requirements

Submit your signed waiver (signed by your parent or guardian) with a photocopy of their ID and your COR.

You may submit your complete requirements on the following schedule at ARH 504 faculty room or ARH Consultation room 506. Please look for the Sports Officers.

Schedule:

Tuesday: 10:30 am – 12:00 nn | 3:00 pm – 6:00 pm

Wednesday: 10:30 am – 6:00 pm

Thursday: 11:00 am – 6:00 pm

2. Attendance Verification
Before we accept your requirements, we will check if your name is on the attendance sheet from the Sports Fest General Orientation. If your name is not on the list, you will not be allowed to join the tryouts.

3. Deadline of Submission
No requirements will be accepted on the day of the tryouts. The last day of submission is Thursday.

4. During Tryouts

Participants are requested to come early for registration and a short briefing.

Orientation will start at 5:00 pm at the ARH 3rd Floor Function Room.

Do not proceed directly to the FEU Court/Quadrangle.

5. Proper Attire
Do not enter the university wearing your jersey. The guards will not allow you entry. Please change inside the campus.

6. In Case of Bad Weather
If classes are not suspended, the tryouts will push through. A Plan B will be implemented and announced during the briefing.

Lastly, during the Sports Fest General Orientation, we provided a QR code to join the official group chat for all attendees. If you are not yet part of it, kindly send us a message on our page.

REMEMBER:
NO ORIENTATION, NO TRYOUTS
NO TRYOUTS, NO SPORTS FEST

You may submit your complete requirements on the following schedule at ARH 504 faculty room or ARH Consultation room 506. Please look for the Sports Officers.

Schedule:

Tuesday: 10:30 am – 12:00 nn | 3:00 pm – 6:00 pm

Wednesday: 10:30 am – 6:00 pm

Thursday: 11:00 am – 6:00 pm

2. Attendance Verification
Before we accept your requirements, we will check if your name is on the attendance sheet from the Sports Fest General Orientation. If your name is not on the list, you will not be allowed to join the tryouts.

3. Deadline of Submission
No requirements will be accepted on the day of the tryouts. The last day of submission is Thursday.

4. During Tryouts

Participants are requested to come early for registration and a short briefing.

Orientation will start at 5:00 pm at the ARH 3rd Floor Function Room.

Do not proceed directly to the FEU Court/Quadrangle.

5. Proper Attire
Do not enter the university wearing your jersey. The guards will not allow you entry. Please change inside the campus.

6. In Case of Bad Weather
If classes are not suspended, the tryouts will push through. A Plan B will be implemented and announced during the briefing.

Lastly, during the Sports Fest General Orientation, we provided a QR code to join the official group chat for all attendees. If you are not yet part of it, kindly send us a message on our page.

REMEMBER:
NO ORIENTATION, NO TRYOUTS

message.text:
Good day ITHM students,

For those who attended the Sports Fest General Orientation last August 27, please take note of the following reminders:

1. Submission of Requirements

Submit your signed waiver (signed by your parent or guardian) with a photocopy of their ID and your COR.

You may submit your complete requirements on the following schedule at ARH 504 faculty room or ARH Consultation room 506. Please look for the Sports Officers.

Schedule:

Tuesday: 10:30 am – 12:00 nn | 3:00 pm – 6:00 pm

Wednesday: 10:30 am – 6:00 pm

Thursday: 11:00 am – 6:00 pm

2. Attendance Verification
Before we accept your requirements, we will check if your name is on the attendance sheet from the Sports Fest General Orientation. If your name is not on the list, you will not be allowed to join the tryouts.

3. Deadline of Submission
No requirements will be accepted on the day of the tryouts. The last day of submission is Thursday.

4. During Tryouts

Participants are requested to come early for registration and a short briefing.

Orientation will start at 5:00 pm at the ARH 3rd Floor Function Room.

Do not proceed directly to the FEU Court/Quadrangle.

5. Proper Attire
Do not enter the university wearing your jersey. The guards will not allow you entry. Please change inside the campus.

6. In Case of Bad Weather
If classes are not suspended, the tryouts will push through. A Plan B will be implemented and announced during the briefing.

Lastly, during the Sports Fest General Orientation, we provided a QR code to join the official group chat for all attendees. If you are not yet part of it, kindly send us a message on our page.

REMEMBER:
NO ORIENTATION, NO TRYOUTS

message.text:
Good day ITHM students,

For those who attended the Sports Fest General Orientation last August 27, please take note of the following reminders:

1. Submission of Requirements

Submit your signed waiver (signed by your parent or guardian) with a photocopy of their ID and your COR.

You may submit your complete requirements on the following schedule at ARH 504 faculty room or ARH Consultation room 506. Please look for the Sports Officers.

Schedule:

Tuesday: 10:30 am – 12:00 nn | 3:00 pm – 6:00 pm

Wednesday: 10:30 am – 6:00 pm

Thursday: 11:00 am – 6:00 pm

2. Attendance Verification
Before we accept your requirements, we will check if your name is on the attendance sheet from the Sports Fest General Orientation. If your name is not on the list, you will not be allowed to join the tryouts.

3. Deadline of Submission
No requirements will be accepted on the day of the tryouts. The last day of submission is Thursday.

4. During Tryouts

Participants are requested to come early for registration and a short briefing.

Orientation will start at 5:00 pm at the ARH 3rd Floor Function Room.

Do not proceed directly to the FEU Court/Quadrangle.

5. Proper Attire
Do not enter the university wearing your jersey. The guards will not allow you entry. Please change inside the campus.

6. In Case of Bad Weather
If classes are not suspended, the tryouts will push through. A Plan B will be implemented and announced during the briefing.

Lastly, during the Sports Fest General Orientation, we provided a QR code to join the official group chat for all attendees. If you are not yet part of it, kindly send us a message on our page.

REMEMBER:
NO ORIENTATION, NO TRYOUTS
NO TRYOUTS, NO SPORTS FEST
